<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-NRwwk6YGAtu25V3Lc04G6w" name="Plan sprint,_4LOggPpaEdqsc-f87sBK8A" guid="-NRwwk6YGAtu25V3Lc04G6w" authors="Easy-Tour" changeDate="2017-07-26T10:51:02.026-0300" version="1.0.0">
  <keyConsiderations>&lt;p>&#xD;
    A reunião de planejamento de sprint é um trabalho em grupo.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Ela é limitada:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Tempo máximo: 4 horas.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Tempo médio: 2 horas.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></keyConsiderations>
  <sections xmi:id="_TJNsUP--Edqtbrr0B1TG-A" name="Definir o objetivo da Sprint" guid="_TJNsUP--Edqtbrr0B1TG-A">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;span lang=&quot;pt&quot; id=&quot;result_box&quot;>&lt;span>No início dos primeiros sprints da primeira versão de um produto, o objetivo é&#xD;
    geralmente mostrar a viabilidade na arquitetura potencial.&lt;/span>&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;span>Então, uma vez que a arquitetura é validada, o objetivo de um sprint é proposto pelo Proprietário do Produto e&#xD;
    discutido com a equipe.&lt;/span> &lt;span>Muitas vezes se concentra em um determinado tema funcional.&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span     role=&quot;button&quot; aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; id=&quot;t-served-community-button&quot; class=&quot;trans-verified-button goog-toolbar-button&quot;     style=&quot;DISPLAY: none; -ms-user-select: none&quot;>&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_xvy5UAPKEdubhrgDuRb4fA" name="Selecionar items" guid="_xvy5UAPKEdubhrgDuRb4fA">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    It is about defining the scope of this sprint. This is done by associating &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../Easy/workproducts/product_backlog_item_C561C125.html&quot; guid=&quot;_-D85cIGIEduKE9hnyImx1Q&quot;>Product Backlog&#xD;
    Item&lt;/a>s one by one &amp;nbsp;to the sprint, and balancing with the team velocity.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If a &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../Easy/guidances/reports/release_planning_ED85F1BB.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_Z2NzkIGWEduKE9hnyImx1Q&quot;>Release planning&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;has been done, this step is only about collectively validating&#xD;
    the forecasted backlog subset for the sprint.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_p4C0sP--Edqtbrr0B1TG-A" name="Identificar tarefas dos items" guid="_p4C0sP--Edqtbrr0B1TG-A">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The 2nd part of the meeting is about defining how the team is gonna achieve the sprint objectives.&lt;br />&#xD;
    To do that, each selected &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../Easy/workproducts/product_backlog_item_C561C125.html&quot; guid=&quot;_-D85cIGIEduKE9hnyImx1Q&quot;>Product Backlog Item&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;is decomposed into tasks. This enables the team to discuss&#xD;
    and figure solutions aspects towards this item, asking the procut owner, if necessary, precisions on the product&#xD;
    behavior.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Normaly, all the lifecycle activities are rolled out during a sprint:&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Selected requirements are specified&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Architecture is modified if necessary&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Classes and subsystems are designed, implemented and tested&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The different components are integrated and tested&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Product is packaged&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Acceptance tests are passed.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The given importance to these activities depends on the position of the sprint within the release.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    The planned work in a previous sprint that couldn't be done because of objectives reduction, becomes the priority for&#xD;
    next sprint.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_DxNQUAPLEdubhrgDuRb4fA" name="Estimar tarefas" guid="_DxNQUAPLEdubhrgDuRb4fA">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Tasks are estimated in hours. Tasks should be thin enough to take less than 16 hours.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Estimation is collectively made by the team. During this discussion, technical aspects are reviewed.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_worbAP--Edqtbrr0B1TG-A" name="Atribuir tarefas" guid="_worbAP--Edqtbrr0B1TG-A">
    <sectionDescription>Once sprint activities are defined, they will be assigned to team members. Activities can be done by one or many persons.&#xD;
All the activities must be taken in to account, including work meetings (non Scrum meetings as well), code or document&#xD;
reviews.&lt;br />&#xD;
It is preferable to delay assignement of certain activities, which will be assigned during the sprint in accordance with&#xD;
team members availability.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_Iq14wAPLEdubhrgDuRb4fA" name="Obter compromisso da equipe" guid="_Iq14wAPLEdubhrgDuRb4fA">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Team should collectively commit to the sprint backlog, that is on backlog items it estimates being able to implement&#xD;
    within the sprint.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>O objetivo é planejar o sprint inicial.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
